3
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:23,732
Me?

4
00:00:23,815 --> 00:00:24,816
LEE SOBIN SURVIVES

5
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:26,693
-Wow.
-Whoa.

6
00:00:28,237 --> 00:00:29,696
Wow, one shot, one kill.

7
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,949
- It was her first time.
- Yes, on her first try.

8
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:34,076
One shot, one kill.

9
00:00:35,244 --> 00:00:36,828
I knew she'd make it.

10
00:00:36,912 --> 00:00:39,206
- With her tiger crystal ball.
- She got it the first time.

11
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:41,375
- That's amazing.
- In one go.

12
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:51,385
Lee Sobin tried just once,
and she got through right away.

13
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:53,971
First try, nailed it.
That felt good to watch.

14
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:56,556
That's what you call a seasoned veteran.

15
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:59,309
You could call that know-how.

16
00:01:00,978 --> 00:01:03,939
Seo Minsu weighed 150 kg,

17
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:05,566
which is considered severely overweight.

18
00:01:05,649 --> 00:01:08,652
So he had a gastrectomy
to improve his health.

19
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,736
GASTRECTOMY IN 2023

20
00:01:11,029 --> 00:01:13,865
- Oh, dear.
- That was it.

21
00:01:18,370 --> 00:01:20,205
I knew it. Gosh…

22
00:01:20,289 --> 00:01:22,874
A gastrectomy. I wrote it down here.

23
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,254
GASTRECTOMY

24
00:01:28,297 --> 00:01:29,298
I wrote it down. See?

25
00:01:29,381 --> 00:01:30,799
- "Gastrectomy," "belly fat."
- Ah!

26
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,848
And due to paralysis
in his arms, shoulders, and neck,

27
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:41,101
he had 2 operations
to treat his cervical discs.

28
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:43,353
Ah!

29
00:01:43,437 --> 00:01:45,564
- That's why he had paralysis.
- Mmm…

30
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:47,733
Ah…

31
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:51,445
Until the very end,
we had a hard time

32
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:53,989
deciding between the 2 of you.

33
00:01:54,072 --> 00:01:55,782
First, I felt chills

34
00:01:55,866 --> 00:01:58,535
when you said the stomach was cut out.

35
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:02,873
And sometimes, doctors put a tube
in the neck to treat cervical discs.

36
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:06,251
For those reasons, we went with Lee Sobin.

37
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:07,419
CORRECT

38
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:10,422
Ineuidang said he had circulation issues

39
00:02:10,505 --> 00:02:11,632
at the back of his neck,

40
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:14,843
and that he got an organ
near the ribs cut out,

41
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:16,887
which was very accurate.

42
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,097
But the body parts weren't quite right,

43
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:21,850
- so unfortunately, we couldn't pick her.
- Right.

44
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:22,934
WRONG

45
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:25,937
Mr. Seo, can you tell us

46
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:28,732
