00:38:51,162 --> 00:38:55,375
I'll do it.

773
00:38:55,458 --> 00:38:57,335
Good for you!

774
00:38:57,418 --> 00:38:59,671
Mr. Kim.

775
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:05,593
Wow, fantastic!

776
00:39:05,677 --> 00:39:09,013
Go, youngest!

777
00:39:09,097 --> 00:39:12,225
- They're all powerful.
- This is crazy.

778
00:39:12,308 --> 00:39:15,854
The Fate Readers
who want to challenge Noh Seulbi are

779
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:17,480
Kim Baekmun

780
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:20,441
and Young Master Jiseon.

781
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:23,695
I looked at you and knew

782
00:39:23,778 --> 00:39:25,488
I could dig through your fate,

783
00:39:25,572 --> 00:39:27,574
so I decided to challenge you.

784
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,621
That's so cool of him.

785
00:39:33,705 --> 00:39:34,873
"Dig through."

786
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:38,459
I don't have a reason.

787
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:41,754
Seulbi, was it?

788
00:39:41,838 --> 00:39:43,423
It's good that she's confident.

789
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:46,217
But she gets on my nerves.

790
00:39:48,344 --> 00:39:49,345
Hello.

791
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:51,431
Things weren't smooth from the very start.

792
00:39:51,514 --> 00:39:53,516
Who are you, Granny or Heavenly Fairy?

793
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:56,728
Whatever you are, you look grumpy.

794
00:39:56,811 --> 00:39:58,187
You're sulky.

795
00:39:59,731 --> 00:40:01,024
She was kind of rude.

796
00:40:01,774 --> 00:40:04,569
But it wasn't me she was being rude to.

797
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,488
She was being rude to my Granny spirit.

798
00:40:08,656 --> 00:40:11,868
This is a survival show, so we're bound
to face each other eventually.

799
00:40:11,951 --> 00:40:14,412
One will survive,
and the other will go down.

800
00:40:15,622 --> 00:40:17,123
I'd like to take her on.

801
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,125
Noh Seulbi.

802
00:40:20,043 --> 00:40:24,380
Name your opponent and explain why.

803
00:40:25,089 --> 00:40:26,257
Young Master Jiseon.

804
00:40:29,052 --> 00:40:30,595
He's 10 years younger than me.

805
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:32,138
How dare he?

806
00:40:33,014 --> 00:40:34,265
I should teach him a lesson.

807
00:40:34,807 --> 00:40:37,352
My goodness.

808
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:42,649
I'm younger, but I'm more experienced,

809
00:40:42,732 --> 00:40:45,151
so I'll dig into her as I read her.

810
00:40:46,152 --> 00:40:47,487
Will this turn into a fight?

811
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:49,489
- I know. They might start fighting.
- So scary!

812
00:40:49,572 --> 00:40:51,199
Sparks are flying.

813
00:40:51,282 --> 00:40:52,951
-It's pretty tense.
-Sparks fly.

814
00:40:53,034 --> 00:40:55,286
Noh Seulbi has been matched

815
00:40:55,370 --> 00:40:58,331
with Young Master Jiseon.

816
00:40:58,414 --> 00:41:01,167
Next up is Sage Cheonmyeong.

817
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:03,294
Please step forward.

818
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:06,714
Mr. Evangelist.

819
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:11,219
- He looks like a little boy.
- He's cute. How adorable.

820
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:14,013
It's like he'll start singing a hymn.

821
00:41:14,097 --> 00:41:15,181
Cheonmyeong the evangelist.

822
00:41:15,807 --> 00:41:18,559
Guess the gender of the baby

823
00:41:18,643 --> 00:41:21,104
that each expectant mother is carrying.

824
00:41:23,356 --> 00:41:24,691
He went to KAIST.

825
00:41:26,526 --> 00:41:28,069
Nubzuki's the mascot

826
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:30,113
of Korea Advanced
Institute of Science and Technology.

827
00:41:30,196 --> 00:41:32,073
I held it and swayed side to side

828
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:34,784
because the Child spirit made me do so.

829
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:36,202
I asked the Child spirit

830
00:41:36,285 --> 00:41:38,121
to show me a peach for a girl

831
00:41:38,204 --> 00:41:40,123
and a chili pepper for a boy.

832
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:43,334
Go Minji and Jo Inhye are having girls

833
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:45,378
and Go Miho is having a boy.

834
00:41:45,461 --> 00:41:46,796
Hey, he's right.

835
00:41:49,257 --> 00:41:50,925
For correctly reading
the babies' genders,

836
00:41:51,009 --> 00:41:53,511
Sage Cheonmyeong survived.

837
00:41:56,139 --> 00:41:57,932
I'm so nervous.

838
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:02,812
When I was given the name
"Sage Cheonmyeong,"

839
00:42:02,895 --> 00:42:04,981
I was told to obey the heavens

840
00:42:05,565 --> 00:42:06,649
and deliver their messages well.

841
00:42:06,733 --> 00:42:09,277
If you would like me

842
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:10,695
to tell your fortune,

843
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:12,780
please come forward.

844
00:42:12,864 --> 00:42:15,575
His soul seemed very clear and pure.

845
00:42:15,658 --> 00:42:19,370
He doesn't have that much experience,

846
00:42:19,454 --> 00:42:23,624
and people like that
rely purely on their deities,

847
00:42:23,708 --> 00:42:25,168
so they're rarely wrong.

848
00:42:25,251 --> 00:42:27,211
There's no beating that.

849
00:42:29,005 --> 00:42:31,799
When Sage Cheonmyeong came forward,

850
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:35,553
my body started trembling,
and it felt like I had to go for it.

851
00:42:41,267 --> 00:42:42,894
TAEUL LEE DOKYU, SEOLHWA

852
00:42:42,977 --> 00:42:48,441
Sage Cheonmyeong,
name your opponent and explain why.

853
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,444
I choose Seolhwa.

854
00:42:54,113 --> 00:42:55,698
I actually got a divine message back there

855
00:42:55,782 --> 00:42:56,783
that you'd challenge me,

856
00:42:56,866 --> 00:42:58,785
-so I was surprised it came true.
-Gosh.

857
00:42:58,868 --> 00:43:00,036
My Granny spirit said,

858
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:04,415
"You'll go up against Seolhwa."

859
00:43:04,499 --> 00:43:06,626
"There's a message you should deliver."

860
00:43:06,709 --> 00:43:09,378
I realized I was meant to take her on.

861
00:43:09,962 --> 00:43:11,714
So I pick Seolhwa.

862
00:43:13,466 --> 00:43:15,551
Sage Cheonmyeong

863
00:43:15,635 --> 00:43:17,637
has been matched with Seolhwa.

864
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:20,681
Next up is Lee Sobin.

865
00:43:20,765 --> 00:43:22,642
Please step forward.

866
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:23,810
LEE SOBIN
20-YEAR SHAMAN

867
00:43:23,893 --> 00:43:25,853
Her presence is definitely powerful.

868
00:43:37,949 --> 00:43:41,410
It's her! The young shaman
who foresaw MC Mong's future.

869
00:43:41,494 --> 00:43:43,496
MC Mong!

870
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:44,580
FORETELLING OF MC MONG'S MISDEED

871
00:43:44,664 --> 00:43:45,832
The child shaman on Star King.

872
00:43:45,915 --> 00:43:47,458
- For real?
- Yes.

873
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:49,669
Her aura is no joke.

874
00:43:49,752 --> 00:43:52,130
For me, Sobin was
the most intimidating shaman of all.

875
00:43:52,213 --> 00:43:55,091
I half-jokingly said I thought she'd win.

876
00:43:55,174 --> 00:43:57,510
- Lee Sobin.
- Lee Sobin.

877
00:43:57,593 --> 00:43:59,595
- Lee Sobin.
- Lee Sobin.

878
00:43:59,679 --> 00:44:01,305
- Lee Sobin.
- Lee Sobin.

879
00:44:01,389 --> 00:44:03,224
Lee Sobin.
She's a strong contender to win.

880
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:23,452
- Tarot masters.
- The tarot masters went for it.

881
00:44:23,953 --> 00:44:25,621
I will go with Rumi.

882
00:44:26,789 --> 00:44:27,790
LEE SOBIN VS RUMI

883
00:44:28,541 --> 00:44:30,960
I'm 1 of those
wide-eyed maniacs, you know.

884
00:44:31,043 --> 00:44:33,462
- I'll beat you.
- She's so tough.

885
00:44:34,463 --> 00:44:36,757
I'm smiling right now,

886
00:44:36,841 --> 00:44:39,010
but Rumi,
I'll be totally different up there.

887
00:44:41,929 --> 00:44:43,973
- She's scary. And feisty.
- I'm scared.

888
00:44:44,056 --> 00:44:46,058
Pie has been matched

889
00:44:46,142 --> 00:44:50,062
with Meta Myungri Joon.

890
00:44:50,146 --> 00:44:52,356
Myungri versus myungri.

891
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:54,400
This should be fun to watch too.

892
00:44:54,483 --> 00:44:56,986
-Definitely. Myungri versus myungri.
-Myungri versus myungri.

893
00:44:57,069 --> 00:45:00,489
Shaman Junghwa has been matched

894
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:01,991
with Yoon Daeman.

895
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:03,326
SHAMAN JUNGHWA VS YOON DAEMAN

896
00:45:03,409 --> 00:45:05,703
Choi Hannah has been matched

897
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:07,163
with Young Master Byeon.

898
00:45:07,246 --> 00:45:08,331
CHOI HANNAH
VS YOUNG MASTER BYEON

899
00:45:08,414 --> 00:45:10,875
Lee Kookjoo has been matched

900
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:12,251
with Kim Baekmun.

901
00:45:12,335 --> 00:45:13,336
LEE KOOKJOO VS KIM BAEKMUN

902
00:45:14,128 --> 00:45:16,714
MATCHUP COMPLETE

903
00:45:17,632 --> 00:45:21,219
We have a new Fate Reaper
joining us starting today.

904
00:45:21,302 --> 00:45:23,846
Introducing Park Haseon.

905
00:45:24,430 --> 00:45:27,308
Hello, I'm Park Haseon.
I'm pleased to meet you.

906
00:45:27,892 --> 00:45:30,770
I'm really excited about today,

907
00:45:30,853 --> 00:45:32,563
but I was actually afraid.

908
00:45:32,647 --> 00:45:36,609
I used to see and feel things as well.

909
00:45:37,401 --> 00:45:39,779
- Mmm.
- I thought so.

910
00:45:39,862 --> 00:45:42,323
When I first met Haseon,

911
00:45:42,823 --> 00:45:45,660
I knew she had an unusual energy.

912
00:45:45,743 --> 00:45:48,287
In our language,
she's open to the spirit world.

913
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:51,123
She has a soft, gentle image as an actor.

914
00:45:51,207 --> 00:45:53,834
But when I saw her
up on the Fate Reaper's seat,

915
00:45:53,918 --> 00:45:56,921
she seemed very strong and firm.

916
00:45:57,004 --> 00:45:59,590
I was pleased to see a Fate Reaper

917
00:45:59,674 --> 00:46:01,384
whom I thought suited the show well.

918
00:46:03,219 --> 00:46:04,804
The Battle of Qi.

919
00:46:07,682 --> 00:46:09,767
The first face-off is

920
00:46:10,268 --> 00:46:12,436
between Sage Cheonmyeong

921
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:13,688
and Seolhwa.

922
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:20,278
He has been a shaman for 10 months.

923
00:46:20,361 --> 00:46:22,780
Isn't it when they're most potent?

924
00:46:22,863 --> 00:46:24,323
- Sage Cheonmyeong. Ten months.
- Yes.

925
00:46:24,407 --> 00:46:26,200
- He's a novice.
- It hasn't been a year yet.

926
00:46:26,284 --> 00:46:28,577
- And Seolhwa is…
- It's her fourth year.

927
00:46:32,665 --> 00:46:35,126
They're setting out their tools.

928
00:46:43,384 --> 00:46:46,304
She's really going
all in with her spirits.

929
00:46:50,016 --> 00:46:52,059
She has a lot of stuff.

930
00:46:52,143 --> 00:46:53,519
Are they all her main tools?

931
00:46:53,602 --> 00:46:54,603
Yes.

932
00:46:58,232 --> 00:47:00,234
Sage Cheonmyeong,
on the other hand,

933
00:47:00,318 --> 00:47:01,861
only has a bead prayer necklace.

934
00:47:02,987 --> 00:47:05,281
I feel like their reading styles
will be totally different.

935
00:47:05,865 --> 00:47:07,700
I think Sage Cheonmyeong will win.

936
00:47:08,909 --> 00:47:10,077
He'll do well.

937
00:47:15,958 --> 00:47:17,918
A face-off between 4 years and 10 months.

938
00:47:22,173 --> 00:47:25,134
These are the rules for the Battle of Qi.

939
00:47:25,843 --> 00:47:27,762
The 20 Fate Readers

940
00:47:27,845 --> 00:47:29,555
will read their opponent.

941
00:47:30,264 --> 00:47:32,892
Not only must you read
their past and present,

942
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:35,144
but you must consult them

943
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:38,105
regarding their most recent
personal contemplation.

944
00:47:41,192 --> 00:47:42,735
The winner of the face-off

945
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:46,739
will be decided by the Fate Reapers' vote.

946
00:47:47,531 --> 00:47:48,741
The Fate Reapers were given

947
00:47:49,241 --> 00:47:52,161
the Book of Fate that has the past
and present records

948
00:47:52,244 --> 00:47:53,829
of every Fate Reader.

949
00:47:53,913 --> 00:47:55,664
Their decisions will be based off

950
00:47:55,748 --> 00:47:58,084
of what's in this book.

951
00:47:58,834 --> 00:48:00,503
After the face-off,

952
00:48:00,586 --> 00:48:03,923
-vote for who you think won
-Oh, we get to choose?

953
00:48:04,006 --> 00:48:06,801
by pressing the button.

954
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:11,097
We will now decide who goes first.

955
00:48:11,180 --> 00:48:12,431
THEY TAKE A CARD AT THE SAME TIME

956
00:48:12,515 --> 00:48:13,516
TO DECIDE WHO GOES FIRST

957
00:48:13,599 --> 00:48:15,726
Select a card.

958
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:18,604
That was aggressive.

959
00:48:19,772 --> 00:48:21,190
Seolhwa goes first.

960
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:23,109
Sage Cheonmyeong goes second.

961
00:48:24,110 --> 00:48:25,444
Is it better to go first?

962
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:28,280
- That could be better.
- Is it?

963
00:48:28,364 --> 00:48:30,866
- Because you can intimidate them first.
- You can intimidate them.

964
00:48:32,493 --> 00:48:34,662
Seolhwa doesn't seem to be nervous at all.

965
00:48:35,746 --> 00:48:37,790
Seolhwa and Sage Cheonmyeong.

966
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:40,459
Please begin.

967
00:48:42,002 --> 00:48:43,170
What's your name?

968
00:48:43,254 --> 00:48:44,255
It's Son Noa.

969
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:45,673
-Son?
-Noa.

970
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:47,341
-Did you change your name?
-Yes.

971
00:48:47,425 --> 00:48:49,301
- What was it before?
- It was Son Changho.

972
00:48:49,385 --> 00:48:50,761
- Son Changho?
- Yes.

973
00:48:50,845 --> 00:48:52,847
She got the name change right away.

974
00:48:52,930 --> 00:48:54,348
She's off to a good start.

975
00:48:54,432 --> 00:48:56,475
- Year of birth?
- 1993--

976
00:48:56,559 --> 00:48:58,894
That'll do.

977
00:49:03,274 --> 00:49:04,650
Let's see.

978
00:49:04,733 --> 00:49:08,404
Granny, Grandpa.
Son Changho, born in 1993.

979
00:49:08,487 --> 00:49:10,865
He changed his name to Son Noa.

980
00:49:10,948 --> 00:49:13,868
Help me speak the truth

981
00:49:13,951 --> 00:49:16,412
and not rely on my human thoughts.

982
00:49:23,586 --> 00:49:25,713
I'd never had
another shaman do a reading on me.

983
00:49:25,796 --> 00:49:29,175
I was nervous and also wondered
if my deities would allow it.

984
00:49:34,889 --> 00:49:37,099
Okay. Sage Cheonmyeong.

985
00:49:37,683 --> 00:49:38,684
Yes.

986
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:43,230
It's weird,
but I don't see you as a shaman.

987
00:49:43,314 --> 00:49:44,690
You are a shaman,

988
00:49:44,773 --> 00:49:47,443
but you have a Granny
wearing a pointy hat.

989
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:50,070
I think she is
your Ancestral Guardian spirit.

990
00:49:50,154 --> 00:49:53,240
That means you do come
from a family of shamans.

991
00:49:54,783 --> 00:49:56,827
His ancestors were shamans.

992
00:49:56,911 --> 00:49:58,329
How can she know that?

993
00:49:58,412 --> 00:49:59,455
She sees it.

994
00:49:59,538 --> 00:50:01,290
SHAMANIC LINEAGE
ON MOTHER'S SIDE

995
00:50:01,373 --> 00:50:03,334
The Granny with the pointy hat

996
00:50:03,417 --> 00:50:05,711
didn't want to make you a shaman.

997
00:50:05,794 --> 00:50:07,379
You were meant to be a monk.

998
00:50:07,463 --> 00:50:10,090
I saw you dressed as a Buddhist monk.

999
00:50:10,633 --> 00:50:13,010
I think that's why you have that necklace.

1000
00:50:13,093 --> 00:50:14,970
I see a moktak.

1001
00:50:15,054 --> 00:50:16,847
I think you serve Buddha too.

1002
00:50:18,933 --> 00:50:20,726
I was actually quite surprised.

1003
00:50:20,809 --> 00:50:22,520
She said she saw Buddha.

1004
00:50:22,603 --> 00:50:24,730
Whether it be Buddhism or Taoism,

1005
00:50:24,813 --> 00:50:27,191
various deities possess me.

1006
00:50:27,274 --> 00:50:29,318
So I was in the situation
where I must study

1007
00:50:29,401 --> 00:50:31,820
the scripture of many religions.

1008
00:50:31,904 --> 00:50:34,490
I thought, "Oh, she got that right."

1009
00:50:34,990 --> 00:50:37,952
I see lots of writings
or documents in your life.

1010
00:50:38,035 --> 00:50:40,079
Maybe there was a scholar in your family

1011
00:50:40,162 --> 00:50:41,747
or someone was in academia.

1012
00:50:41,830 --> 00:50:43,791
What do you call that again?
A graduation cap?

1013
00:50:43,874 --> 00:50:45,167
My father also has a PhD.

1014
00:50:45,668 --> 00:50:48,504
My gosh. It runs in the family, huh?

1015
00:50:48,587 --> 00:50:50,339
That's why you're good at this.

1016
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:52,007
He'll make a great shaman!

1017
00:50:54,385 --> 00:50:57,137
So, my family…

1018
00:50:57,221 --> 00:50:59,014
My grandfather taught Confucianism.

1019
00:50:59,098 --> 00:51:01,016
My great-grandfather before him too.

1020
00:51:01,100 --> 00:51:04,979
And my father used to work at a bank.

1021
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:08,190
He got his PhD in Accounting around
the time he quit as a sub branch manager.

1022
00:51:08,274 --> 00:51:11,193
He's a professor now.

1023
00:51:12,444 --> 00:51:14,572
It's a family of scholars.

1024
00:51:16,782 --> 00:51:18,200
I see lots of things.

1025
00:51:18,284 --> 00:51:20,160
I saw something like needles.

1026
00:51:20,244 --> 00:51:22,955
It's like you are
a traditional Korean medicine doctor.

1027
00:51:23,038 --> 00:51:25,833
He's thinking about becoming one.

1028
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:27,167
A traditional Korean medicine doctor.

1029
00:51:27,251 --> 00:51:28,961
What, really?

1030
00:51:29,044 --> 00:51:31,213
He was actually thinking about it.

1031
00:51:31,297 --> 00:51:32,756
What the heck is this?

1032
00:51:33,924 --> 00:51:35,759
He wanted to study Korean medicine.

1033
00:51:36,385 --> 00:51:38,220
Yes, that's right.

1034
00:51:38,304 --> 00:51:39,638
Even if it's not as a shaman,

1035
00:51:39,722 --> 00:51:41,974
you could save people

1036
00:51:42,057 --> 00:51:45,603
and probably help legally as well.

1037
00:51:46,770 --> 00:51:48,439
Wait, why does the Child spirit…

1038
00:51:48,522 --> 00:51:50,232
He must want to say something.

1039
00:51:50,316 --> 00:51:52,067
Oh, another spirit.

1040
00:51:52,151 --> 00:51:54,486
- This is fascinating.
- Another spirit's here.

1041
00:51:55,946 --> 00:51:57,615
Hey, did you fail 3 times?

1042
00:51:58,282 --> 00:51:59,366
Three times?

1043
00:52:04,455 --> 00:52:05,664
That's right.

1044
00:52:05,748 --> 00:52:08,083
You failed 3 times when you were 20.

1045
00:52:08,167 --> 00:52:09,918
- When he was 20?
- Failed what?

1046
00:52:13,881 --> 00:52:16,342
- The 3 questions he got wrong?
- The 3 wrong answers?

1047
00:52:16,425 --> 00:52:18,594
The 3 questions he got wrong in the CSAT?

1048
00:52:18,677 --> 00:52:20,304
One each in Korean, English, and Math.

1049
00:52:21,513 --> 00:52:23,182
Gosh. She got this?

1050
00:52:23,265 --> 00:52:24,642
HE GOT 3 QUESTIONS WRONG IN THE CSAT

1051
00:52:24,725 --> 00:52:28,187
I don't know what it is,
but you failed at something 3 times.

1052
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:30,606
You're smart and handsome.

1053
00:52:30,689 --> 00:52:32,816
But sorry,
I don't see girls in your lifetime.

1054
00:52:34,818 --> 00:52:37,279
I sense that you've never really dated.

1055
00:52:37,363 --> 00:52:40,115
- Oh…
- So if you ever date a woman,

1056
00:52:40,199 --> 00:52:42,701
she's likely to be
the only woman in your life.

1057
00:52:42,785 --> 00:52:45,496
You won't be jumping
from 1 woman to another.

1058
00:52:45,579 --> 00:52:46,914
Yes, that's true.

1059
00:52:48,832 --> 00:52:51,168
- He answers every question so well.
- Yes.

1060
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:53,921
Your fate renders you
to date older women.

1061
00:52:54,004 --> 00:52:57,257
So you need to take the lead sometimes,

1062
00:52:57,341 --> 00:52:59,426
but you only do that with deities,

1063
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:01,428
and you can't lead your woman.

1064
00:53:02,054 --> 00:53:03,222
- Well…
- What?

1065
00:53:03,305 --> 00:53:05,391
My partner is 5 years older than me,

1066
00:53:05,474 --> 00:53:07,518
but I wear the pants in the house.

1067
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:14,274
Anyone who says that they wear the pants

1068
00:53:14,358 --> 00:53:16,652
-are never really in control.
-They only say they are.

1069
00:53:17,820 --> 00:53:20,072
- I wear the pants in the house.
- You do?

1070
00:53:20,155 --> 00:53:22,032
Gosh, I'm sorry to say this,

1071
00:53:22,116 --> 00:53:23,742
-Yes?
-but you can't be in control.

1072
00:53:24,493 --> 00:53:28,288
You're fated to date an older woman
or someone with such energy.

1073
00:53:28,372 --> 00:53:30,833
That means you should give in,

1074
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:34,294
but you want to take control
because you're a shaman.

1075
00:53:34,378 --> 00:53:35,504
That's greedy of you.

1076
00:53:35,587 --> 00:53:37,840
Right, I see.

1077
00:53:38,632 --> 00:53:41,427
She was so eloquent.
I couldn't help but nod along.

1078
00:53:41,510 --> 00:53:43,387
He's acting like a client.

1079
00:53:44,179 --> 00:53:46,390
She's such a smooth talker.

1080
00:53:46,932 --> 00:53:49,226
I'm just listening and I feel bewitched.

1081
00:53:49,810 --> 00:53:51,562
- She's so good.
- This is great fun.

1082
00:53:52,479 --> 00:53:56,316
Seolhwa, please give him
advice on his recent contemplations.

1083
00:53:57,109 --> 00:54:00,529
If you have anything on your mind,
will you tell me about it?

1084
00:54:00,612 --> 00:54:03,532
The reason I became a shaman

1085
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:06,285
was my sister. I have a younger sister.

1086
00:54:06,368 --> 00:54:08,078
She suffered

1087
00:54:08,162 --> 00:54:11,206
from schizophrenia since she was 17.

1088
00:54:11,290 --> 00:54:14,418
Last August, my Guardian spirit said

1089
00:54:14,501 --> 00:54:17,546
if I didn't become a shaman this time,

1090
00:54:17,629 --> 00:54:20,299
my mom's illness would get worse

1091
00:54:20,382 --> 00:54:22,843
and she'd die,

1092
00:54:22,926 --> 00:54:25,137
and that my sister would be next.

1093
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:27,806
That's why I became a shaman.

1094
00:54:28,932 --> 00:54:30,684
My sister has gotten much better,

1095
00:54:30,768 --> 00:54:33,061
but she doesn't have a decent job yet.

1096
00:54:33,145 --> 00:54:36,899
I'd like to know
what kind of life she'll lead.

1097
00:54:36,982 --> 00:54:39,860
-She's 30 now, born in 1996.
-The Year of the Rat.

1098
00:54:41,945 --> 00:54:45,782
Granny, Grandpa.
Born in the Year of the Rat, 1996.

1099
00:54:50,621 --> 00:54:52,122
She's drawing her obanggi.

1100
00:54:55,709 --> 00:54:57,252
The schizophrenia's long gone.

1101
00:54:58,045 --> 00:54:59,046
My gosh.

1102
00:55:00,255 --> 00:55:01,632
It's gone.

1103
00:55:01,715 --> 00:55:04,176
So why is she still not working?

1104
00:55:06,094 --> 00:55:08,222
She was ill for long,

1105
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:09,890
so she seems
to find it hard to break free.

1106
00:55:10,599 --> 00:55:13,936
I think she's too proud

1107
00:55:14,019 --> 00:55:15,562
to work under anyone.

1108
00:55:15,646 --> 00:55:18,607
I don't see her trying
to join a company or anything.

1109
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:20,192
See this?

1110
00:55:20,275 --> 00:55:21,360
She can't be an employee.

1111
00:55:21,443 --> 00:55:24,279
Make lots of money
and open a shop for her.

1112
00:55:24,363 --> 00:55:26,323
-Oh, okay.
-That's the best solution.

1113
00:55:26,949 --> 00:55:30,244
-I must work hard, then.
-Yes. Your deities will make you rich.

1114
00:55:32,079 --> 00:55:34,164
She's making money without doing anything.

1115
00:55:34,248 --> 00:55:37,793
I think it's because our dad
gives her an allowance.

1116
00:55:37,876 --> 00:55:40,170
That's why the brat won't work.

1117
00:55:42,881 --> 00:55:45,384
People don't take action
when they're too comfortable.

1118
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:47,010
You've got to cut off that pattern.

1119
00:55:47,094 --> 00:55:48,095
Okay.

1120
00:55:49,012 --> 00:55:50,556
Bring her to me later.

1121
00:55:50,639 --> 00:55:52,266
She'll listen to a woman.

1122
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,726
I can talk sense into her.

1123
00:55:54,810 --> 00:55:56,061
So liberating.

1124
00:55:57,688 --> 00:56:00,607
There's nothing I can do
to help you right now,

1125
00:56:00,691 --> 00:56:02,234
but please don't worry.

1126
00:56:02,317 --> 00:56:03,944
She turned polite all of a sudden.

1127
00:56:04,444 --> 00:56:07,489
She switches between characters
so drastically.

1128
00:56:08,115 --> 00:56:09,324
All right, that's all.

1129
00:56:09,408 --> 00:56:11,410
Thank you.

1130
00:56:11,493 --> 00:56:13,745
She spoke so fast.

1131
00:56:13,829 --> 00:56:15,622
It feels like he should pay her.

1132
00:56:16,540 --> 00:56:18,834
- She made a strong first move.
- Yes.

1133
00:56:18,917 --> 00:56:19,918
You can't beat that.

1134
00:56:20,002 --> 00:56:22,045
That was refreshing. I want to go see her.

1135
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:26,008
- That was so direct.
- It was a good reading.

1136
00:56:27,843 --> 00:56:30,887
I was surprised she got
a lot right about my sister.

1137
00:56:30,971 --> 00:56:33,765
She tells fortunes like a real shaman.

1138
00:56:33,849 --> 00:56:34,891
That might sound strange,

1139
00:56:34,975 --> 00:56:37,269
but there's a stereotype
people have of shamans,

1140
00:56:37,352 --> 00:56:39,563
and she matched it exactly.

1141
00:56:39,646 --> 00:56:41,607
Her style is different from mine.

1142
00:56:41,690 --> 00:56:44,443
I decided to beat her with my own method.

1143
00:56:45,277 --> 00:56:48,905
No one can beat my deities.

1144
00:56:48,989 --> 00:56:50,115
I was confident.

1145
00:56:50,198 --> 00:56:53,368
Sage Cheonmyeong,
please begin your reading.

1146
00:56:55,621 --> 00:56:58,832
- Can I ask how long you've done this for?
- Me?

1147
00:56:58,915 --> 00:57:02,044
- About 3 to 4 years.
- Okay, I see.

1148
00:57:03,128 --> 00:57:05,005
I've never told a shaman's fortune before.

1149
00:57:05,088 --> 00:57:06,632
I'm worried I'll mess up.

1150
00:57:19,978 --> 00:57:24,149
When Sage Cheonmyeong started to read me,

1151
00:57:24,232 --> 00:57:26,068
his expression changed completely.

1152
00:57:35,994 --> 00:57:37,579
The first thing I got

1153
00:57:38,497 --> 00:57:41,541
was that the spirits actually came to you
when you were 17.

1154
00:57:44,753 --> 00:57:46,046
That's when
she started seeing things.

1155
00:57:47,255 --> 00:57:48,548
STARTED SEEING SPIRITS AT 17

1156
00:57:48,632 --> 00:57:50,008
-What?
-No way.

1157
00:57:51,635 --> 00:57:55,013
It seems you tried to divert
your spiritual energy into something else

1158
00:57:55,097 --> 00:57:57,140
but ended up becoming a shaman
3, 4 years ago.

1159
00:57:57,224 --> 00:57:58,767
My Granny spirit told me

1160
00:57:58,850 --> 00:58:01,353
why you became a shaman.

1161
00:58:02,062 --> 00:58:05,148
You weren't fated to live long.

1162
00:58:07,818 --> 00:58:08,944
And another thing.

1163
00:58:09,027 --> 00:58:11,154
This is what your Guardian spirit said.

1164
00:58:11,238 --> 00:58:12,239
"If my dear…"

1165
00:58:13,198 --> 00:58:15,617
-I'll just say exactly what she said.
-Okay.

1166
00:58:15,701 --> 00:58:18,245
"If my dear Seolhwa

1167
00:58:18,328 --> 00:58:20,330
had kept going the way she was,

1168
00:58:20,414 --> 00:58:23,542
her heart
would've gone into overdrive at 37."

1169
00:58:23,625 --> 00:58:24,876
"That's why

1170
00:58:24,960 --> 00:58:28,338
I made her a shaman, to keep her alive."

1171
00:58:29,381 --> 00:58:31,717
I knew I wasn't meant to live long,

1172
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:34,219
but it was the first time
someone actually told me that.

1173
00:58:34,302 --> 00:58:37,055
I was really surprised when he said that.

1174
00:58:38,348 --> 00:58:42,060
And he pinpointed the age of 37.

1175
00:58:42,144 --> 00:58:43,395
I'd been feeling

1176
00:58:43,478 --> 00:58:45,814
someone would die
when I turned 37 and I'd been worried.

1177
00:58:45,897 --> 00:58:48,942
He was saying that could've been me.

1178
00:58:49,818 --> 00:58:51,319
It was really shocking.

1179
00:58:53,321 --> 00:58:54,614
That's her concern.

1180
00:58:54,698 --> 00:58:56,742
- What? Her concern.
- At age 37.

1181
00:58:56,825 --> 00:58:58,910
She's worried about when she's 37.

1182
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,913
I got the chills!

1183
00:59:01,997 --> 00:59:03,039
Oh, goosebumps.

1184
00:59:03,665 --> 00:59:06,042
It doesn't usually happen,
but if there's a connection,

1185
00:59:06,710 --> 00:59:09,337
I can communicate
with the other person's deity.

1186
00:59:09,421 --> 00:59:11,214
As soon as I sat down,

1187
00:59:11,298 --> 00:59:14,217
I saw her Guardian spirit
in a white pointy hat.

1188
00:59:14,301 --> 00:59:16,386
She told me what she wanted me to say.

1189
00:59:16,470 --> 00:59:20,265
I thought, "So this is why my
Granny spirit told me to go against her."

1190
00:59:23,852 --> 00:59:25,979
What's your concern, Seolhwa?

1191
00:59:26,062 --> 00:59:28,023
In my case…

1192
00:59:28,106 --> 00:59:31,943
They say female shamans go through
a hard time at ages ending in 7.

1193
00:59:33,278 --> 00:59:36,364
A lot of bad things
happened to me in those years.

1194
00:59:36,448 --> 00:59:40,076
My really close friends
all took their own lives.

1195
00:59:50,295 --> 00:59:51,338
Seolhwa.

1196
00:59:51,838 --> 00:59:52,964
Yes?

1197
00:59:53,048 --> 00:59:55,634
This might be difficult
for you to answer,

1198
00:59:55,717 --> 00:59:58,053
but did you lose someone special

1199
00:59:58,136 --> 01:00:02,098
each time your age ended in 7?

1200
01:00:02,182 --> 01:00:05,894
Yes. When I was 17,
I only had this 1 friend.

1201
01:00:05,977 --> 01:00:07,354
I kept seeing her

1202
01:00:07,437 --> 01:00:10,065
walking around in an apartment building.

1203
01:00:10,148 --> 01:00:11,149
Oh, dear.

1204
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:13,443
After that,

1205
01:00:13,527 --> 01:00:16,279
her mom called me,
and I just burst into tears.

1206
01:00:17,072 --> 01:00:18,573
As soon as I heard the phone ring.

1207
01:00:19,407 --> 01:00:21,743
Mmm.
Before she even heard the news.

1208
01:00:21,827 --> 01:00:22,911
She just knew.

1209
01:00:25,872 --> 01:00:29,376
I saw a vision then.

1210
01:00:30,001 --> 01:00:31,837
And I lost another friend when I was 27.

1211
01:00:32,546 --> 01:00:34,464
For a moment, I saw her

1212
01:00:34,548 --> 01:00:36,341
as she was when she died.

1213
01:00:40,303 --> 01:00:41,429
So…

1214
01:00:42,013 --> 01:00:44,641
I could picture which room in the house

1215
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,435
it happened in because I knew
what her house looked like.

1216
01:00:47,519 --> 01:00:50,730
So I asked her older sister,
"Is this how she died?"

1217
01:00:51,690 --> 01:00:52,858
And she said I was right.

1218
01:00:52,941 --> 01:00:54,192
I couldn't understand.

1219
01:00:54,276 --> 01:00:57,445
"Why do I see things
that aren't my thoughts?"

1220
01:00:58,405 --> 01:00:59,823
Well, that's what happened.

1221
01:01:05,912 --> 01:01:07,706
I can relate to her stories.

1222
01:01:08,248 --> 01:01:09,416
My heart breaks.

1223
01:01:10,834 --> 01:01:13,086
Shamans seem to have
many tragic stories.

1224
01:01:18,300 --> 01:01:22,721
So I'm afraid of people dying
and leaving me.

1225
01:01:22,804 --> 01:01:25,557
So, when I'm approaching the age of 37…

1226
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:27,267
I have just 1 friend.

1227
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:29,144
-I don't think she'll die.
-Right.

1228
01:01:29,227 --> 01:01:31,646
But someone around me,

1229
01:01:31,730 --> 01:01:33,481
like my family.

1230
01:01:33,565 --> 01:01:36,818
-There are people I must protect.
-Yes.

1231
01:01:36,902 --> 01:01:39,654
Is there a chance of me losing my family?

1232
01:01:39,738 --> 01:01:42,282
She must be so anxious.

1233
01:01:42,365 --> 01:01:44,326
Yes. I'd be so afraid.

1234
01:02:02,010 --> 01:02:04,930
I guess I'm here
just so I can give you this message.

1235
01:02:11,603 --> 01:02:13,438
Your family will be safe.

1236
01:02:13,521 --> 01:02:15,440
The Guardian spirit says
she will protect them.

1237
01:02:15,982 --> 01:02:17,025
- She will?
- Yes.

1238
01:02:17,108 --> 01:02:19,653
Thank you. Your Guardian spirit or mine?

1239
01:02:21,613 --> 01:02:23,323
Oh, my gosh.

1240
01:02:30,038 --> 01:02:32,290
-If she can protect my family,
-Yes.

1241
01:02:32,374 --> 01:02:34,292
I'll keep praying and holding on to her.

1242
01:02:35,085 --> 01:02:38,838
I pray to communicate with my deities.

1243
01:02:38,922 --> 01:02:40,340
Of course, they tell me

1244
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:43,051
they'll help and protect me.

1245
01:02:43,134 --> 01:02:45,178
But I am only human,

1246
01:02:46,471 --> 01:02:47,889
so I become doubtful sometimes.

1247
01:02:47,973 --> 01:02:50,225
But when…

1248
01:02:50,308 --> 01:02:54,187
He told me that my Guardian spirit
would protect me,

1249
01:02:54,270 --> 01:02:56,314
as if he were her messenger.

1250
01:02:56,398 --> 01:02:58,066
I was so grateful.

1251
01:02:59,526 --> 01:03:01,987
- That'd be all.
- Thank you.

1252
01:03:03,613 --> 01:03:05,073
That one hit hard.

1253
01:03:05,699 --> 01:03:07,784
That was a close match.

1254
01:03:07,867 --> 01:03:10,245
He spoke calmly but got really deep.

1255
01:03:10,328 --> 01:03:11,329
Yes.

1256
01:03:12,372 --> 01:03:15,166
Fate Reapers.

1257
01:03:15,250 --> 01:03:18,420
Between Seolhwa and Sage Cheonmyeong,

1258
01:03:18,503 --> 01:03:20,672
choose the survivor.

1259
01:03:21,589 --> 01:03:23,133
What do I do?

1260
01:03:26,011 --> 01:03:27,095
What do we do?

1261
01:03:28,722 --> 01:03:31,057
It's hard. This is so hard.

1262
01:03:33,351 --> 01:03:34,644
What do I do?

1263
01:03:35,812 --> 01:03:37,230
Based on the flow of qi.

1264
01:03:37,313 --> 01:03:39,149
- This is the Battle of Qi.
- Yes.

1265
01:03:39,232 --> 01:03:40,233
Shall we vote?

1266
01:03:43,403 --> 01:03:44,446
I must choose.

1267
01:03:47,282 --> 01:03:48,283
It's hard.

1268
01:03:49,951 --> 01:03:51,077
They both did well.

1269
01:03:53,872 --> 01:03:55,373
The Battle of Qi.

1270
01:03:56,958 --> 01:03:58,251
Here we go.

1271
01:04:07,093 --> 01:04:09,637
The winner of the 1-on-1 face-off is…

1272
01:04:11,973 --> 01:04:15,769
Seolhwa?
Cheonmyeong? Who is it?

1273
01:04:16,561 --> 01:04:17,562
I'm trembling.

1274
01:04:18,313 --> 01:04:20,356
I don't know who the others voted for.

1275
01:04:23,068 --> 01:04:24,569
I did my part.

1276
01:04:26,321 --> 01:04:28,156
My deities told me everything.

1277
01:04:28,239 --> 01:04:30,700
I've got to trust my Granny
and Grandpa on this, right?

1278
01:04:36,873 --> 01:04:38,166
SEOLHWA

1279
01:04:41,294 --> 01:04:42,462
SAGE CHEONMYEONG

1280
01:04:53,431 --> 01:04:54,432
SEOLHWA

1281
01:04:54,516 --> 01:04:55,517
SEOLHWA

1282
01:04:56,768 --> 01:04:58,561
Oh, my!

1283
01:05:00,730 --> 01:05:02,899
The winner is Seolhwa.

1284
01:05:05,693 --> 01:05:08,071
SEOLHWA SURVIVES

1285
01:05:08,822 --> 01:05:10,281
Well done.

1286
01:05:11,783 --> 01:05:14,869
The things that Seolhwa said.

1287
01:05:14,953 --> 01:05:17,664
She got the details
that weren't even in the Book of Fate.

1288
01:05:17,747 --> 01:05:21,709
The only way to describe it
is that she poured out all the facts.

1289
01:05:21,793 --> 01:05:25,296
It felt so good and satisfying.

1290
01:05:25,380 --> 01:05:26,714
Thank you.

1291
01:05:28,424 --> 01:05:30,802
I think our Guardian spirits
got along well.

1292
01:05:30,885 --> 01:05:32,345
It wasn't hard.

1293
01:05:32,428 --> 01:05:33,638
I trusted my Granny.

1294
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:38,017
They look like they're in the zone.

1295
01:05:38,101 --> 01:05:39,602
This is the real big match.

1296
01:05:42,647 --> 01:05:44,440
- This is huge.
- What a matchup.

1297
01:05:45,900 --> 01:05:47,193
This is huge.

1298
01:05:47,986 --> 01:05:49,946
Talk about a power matchup.

1299
01:05:50,029 --> 01:05:51,364
Kiddo.

1300
01:05:52,323 --> 01:05:53,491
The Granny's here.

1301
01:05:53,575 --> 01:05:55,785
If your opponent is good,
just tear them down.

1302
01:05:55,869 --> 01:05:56,870
I came well-prepared.

1303
01:05:57,745 --> 01:05:59,873
My eyes rolled back.

1304
01:06:00,456 --> 01:06:01,457
You have the fateof a beggar.

1305
01:06:03,251 --> 01:06:04,502
For real?

1306
01:06:04,586 --> 01:06:06,337
Do you think that's what a shaman does?

1307
01:06:06,421 --> 01:06:07,964
Don't underestimate me.

1308
01:06:08,047 --> 01:06:09,340
You won't respect my deities?

1309
01:06:09,424 --> 01:06:11,718
The tension is no joke.

1310
01:06:11,801 --> 01:06:14,762
This isn't a deity. I want to throw up.

1311
01:06:14,846 --> 01:06:16,264
Screw this.

1312
01:06:17,974 --> 01:06:19,475
What happened? What's wrong?

1313
01:06:19,559 --> 01:06:20,602
She's crying?

1314
01:06:23,771 --> 01:06:25,815
Can I have a moment? Sorry.

1315
01:07:24,666 --> 01:07:26,668
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
